## Docker Setup

A `docker-compose.yml` is provided for local development.

```bash
# Start all services
docker compose up -d

# Run console commands inside the PHP container
docker compose exec php php bin/console <command>

# View logs
docker compose logs -f php
```

Services included:

| Service | Port | Description |
|---------|------|-------------|
| php | 8000 | PHP-FPM + Symfony |
{% if database == "postgresql" %}
| postgres | 5432 | PostgreSQL database |
{% elif database == "mysql" %}
| mysql | 3306 | MySQL database |
{% elif database == "mariadb" %}
| mariadb | 3306 | MariaDB database |
{% endif %}
{% if use_redis %}
| redis | 6379 | Redis cache/sessions |
{% endif %}
{% if use_rabbitmq %}
| rabbitmq | 5672 | RabbitMQ message broker |
| rabbitmq-mgmt | 15672 | RabbitMQ management UI |
{% endif %}

